Meanwhile, in another part of the world, citizens and astronomers in Chile and parts of Argentina got to witness a partial solar eclipse just before sundown today.

This was the first solar eclipse of 2022. Fun fact.

For us Americans, the next solar eclipses are set to occur on October 14, 2023 and April 8, 2024, respectively.

Texans will have the benefit of being able to view both eclipses, with their paths of totality intersecting just west of San Antonio.
